						<h3>What to do if you feel heavy in your legs</h3>
						<figure>
							<img src="./img/image00075.jpg" alt="">
						</figure>
						 <strong>What to do if you feel heavy in your legs</strong><p><span>Blood flows through the veins with the help of valves and, if they work well, then you will not have such a problem.</span></p><p><span>If the heaviness in the legs is still there, it may be due to the fact that the valves work poorly and the blood stagnates in the legs. This happens when the veins expand, on the heat and poor muscle function. If the leg muscles work well, then the valves and blood circulation work well.</span></p><figure><div><div></div><div><img></div><div></div></div><meta><figcaption><span>www.freeimages.com</span></figcaption></figure><h3><span>If there is such a problem, then:</span></h3><ul><li><span>Try to avoid heat and hot baths, saunas and steam rooms. The heat makes the veins dilate, and the blood circulation will be even worse.</span></li><li><span>Pay attention that the clothes do not press anywhere and do not constrict the vessels. This interferes with blood circulation.</span></li><li><span>For the same reason, do not cross your legs when sitting.</span></li><li><span>If you have a sedentary job, then try to get up at least once an hour, stretch a little and walk. During work with your feet do simple exercises. Pull the socks towards and away from you â€” repeat 5-10 times. Make circular movements with your feet in one direction and in the other, also 5-10 times.</span></li><li><span>Try to monitor the weight, so that the load of the leg does not increase.</span></li></ul><h3><span>It will be useful:</span></h3><ul><li><span>It is better to take a shower, rather than a bath and in in the process of massaging the legs with cool water in the direction from the bottom up.</span></li><li><span>If you spend a lot of time on your feet, it is good to wear compression stockings. The degree of compression should be selected by a phlebologist.</span></li><li><span>When flying, compression stockings are mandatory. Even for prevention.</span></li><li><span>Try a little more to go. The recommendation to take 10 thousand steps is not without meaning. This is a good workout for the leg muscles, and therefore the valves in the veins. And good prevention of problems with the cardiovascular system. If you don't practice such long walks, then start with less. Set yourself a bar of 6-7 thousand to begin with. It's not as much as it looks.</span></li><li><span>And, of course, you need comfortable shoes, so that the blood circulation is good and it is not difficult to walk 10 thousand steps.</span></li></ul><p><span><i>Here is another interesting article on the topic - </i></span><span></span><a><i>Edema and what to do with them</i></a><span><i> - I wrote it after a conversation with the surgeon phlebologist.</i></span></p><p><span><b>If you were interested, then put a like, then your feed will contain more of this information.</b></span></p><p><span>And subscribe! I have a lot of exercises here to preserve the beauty and youth of the face :)</span></p><p><span></span></p><div></div>
